Troubleshoot Messaging for In-App and Web Setup

This article applies to: Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels. It doesn't apply to Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

ERROR MESSAGE	SOLUTION

Refused to frame ‘<your ESW_[deploymentname] site>’ because an ancestor violates the following content security policy directive: “frame ancestors <your old domain> <your old subdomain>"
Change or add the domain that’s associated with your embedded service deployment. Go to Setup | User Interface | Sites and Domains | Sites, select your site, find and edit the trusted domain, and save.

Access to XMLHttpRequest at '<your ESW_[deploymentname]_[numbers] site>' from directive: '<your domain>' has been blocked by CORS policy: No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested resource. Add your new domain to the CORS allowlist. From Setup, enter CORS in the Quick Find box, select CORS, click New, enter an origin URL pattern, and save.

Refused to load the script '<your ESW_[deploymentname]_[numbers]>/assets/js/bootstrap.min.js' because it violates the following Content Security Policy directive: "scrtipt-src 'self ''unsafe-eval 'unsafe-inline'...". Add the ESW site as a trusted site within the Builder. Go to Setup | Digital Experiences | All Sites, click Builder next to your experience cloud site, set Security level to Relaxed CSP, add the ESW site details, and publish.

Add the ESW site as a Trusted URL in Setup: Go to Setup | Security | Trusted URLs, click New Trusted URL, fill out the API Name and URL fields, select Experience Builder Sites, and save your changes.
title: Troubleshooting Messaging for In-App and Web Setup
